In [3]:
plt.figure(figsize=(5,5), dpi=600)
sns.set(font='sans serif')
sns.set(style="whitegrid")

ax=sns.barplot(data=M1, x=M1['Condition'], y=(M1['Organelle+Protein+']/M1['Cells'])*100, hue=M1['Organelle'],palette=["#ff4c4c", "#008080"], ci=None)

sample_sizes = [475, 231, 272] 

for p, n in zip(ax.patches, sample_sizes):
    ax.text(
        p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2.,  # X position: center of the bar
        p.get_height() + 1,              # Y position: slightly above the bar
        f'n={n}',                        # Text format, adjust if needed
        ha='center', va='bottom',        # Center align horizontally and slightly above
        fontsize=10                      # Font size for the text
    )
    

handles, labels = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()
new_labels = ['LD+', 'LE+'] 
ax.legend(handles, new_labels, title='iNOS+ cells', fontsize=10, title_fontsize=12)

hue_comparisons = [
    (("mock", "Lipid droplet"), ("mock", "Endosome")),
    (("LPS 6h", "Lipid droplet"), ("LPS 6h", "Endosome")),
    (("LPS 24h", "Lipid droplet"), ("LPS 24h", "Endosome")),
]

# Add hue-specific comparisons
annotator = Annotator(ax, hue_comparisons, data=M1, x='Condition', y=(M1['Organelle+Protein+']/M1['Cells'])*100, hue='Organelle')
annotator.configure(test='t-test_ind', text_format='star', loc='inside', verbose=2)
annotator.apply_and_annotate()

comparisons = [("mock", "LPS 6h"), ("LPS 6h", "LPS 24h"), ("mock","LPS 24h")]

annotator = Annotator(ax, comparisons, data=M1, x="Condition", y=(M1['Organelle+Protein+']/M1['Cells'])*100)
annotator.configure(test='t-test_ind', text_format='star', loc='inside', verbose=2)
annotator.apply_and_annotate()

ax.tick_params(axis='x', labelsize=15)
ax.tick_params(axis='y', labelsize=15)
plt.ylabel('iNOS+ cells containing organelles(%)', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('')
plt.ylim(0,100)

plt.savefig('F:\\Microglia project\\Light microscopy\\Acquifer Data\\Correlative Analysis\\Graphs\\M1_LD_LE_sum(%).png',dpi=600, bbox_inches='tight')

    ax.text(
        p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2.,  # X position: center of the bar
        p.get_height() + 1,              # Y position: slightly above the bar
        f'n={n}',                        # Text format, adjust if needed
        ha='center', va='bottom',        # Center align horizontally and slightly above

    )
